supervisions.notes: The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  Defendant was ordered to report immediately to the probation and parole office.

miscConds.notes:
All Restitution to be paid to the victim(s) first. Private entities, insurance companies or Crime Witness Compensation Programs to be paid second. Fine and court costs to be paid third.
$557.00 of bond previously paid applied to restitution and issued to Case Remit Dept

Fine and/or costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.  Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions.

Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request
Defendant is specifically allowed contact with the victim unless the agent finds a new incident/factors to deny contact.
The defendant is to submit to an Alcohol and Other Drug Assessment (AODA) and follow the recommendations, releasing the findings to the agent.
